  "local_port": 52754,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "I'm doing my first pyromancer build in Dark Souls 3. What stats do I need to build on to be most effective?",
  "response": "Building an effective pyromancer in **Dark Souls 3** focuses primarily on optimizing your character's stats to maximize your pyromancy damage while ensuring survivability and sufficient casting capability. Here's a breakdown of the key stats and considerations to help you create a powerful pyromancer build:\n\n### **1. Intelligence**\n- **Primary Stat for Damage:** In Dark Souls 3, pyromancies scale exclusively with **Intelligence**. Investing heavily in Intelligence will increase the potency of your fire-based spells, making it the cornerstone of your pyromancer build.\n- **Recommended Allocation:** Aim to raise Intelligence to at least **30-40**, depending on your desired power level and late-game requirements. Beyond this, you can continue to invest as high as possible, especially if you plan to use advanced pyromancies.\n\n### **2. Mind**\n- **FP for Casting:** **Mind** increases your Focus Points (FP), which are essential for casting pyromancies. Without sufficient Mind, your casting ability will be limited.\n- **Recommended Allocation:** Balance your Mind to ensure you have enough FP to cast multiple spells in succession. A range of **15-25** is typically effective, but adjust based on your playstyle and the pyromancies you use most frequently.\n\n### **3. Vigor**\n- **Survivability:** **Vigor** raises your health pool, which is crucial for surviving encounters, especially since pyromancers are often more vulnerable due to their reliance on casting.\n- **Recommended Allocation:** Prioritize **Vigor** to ensure you have a solid HP pool. Aim for at least **27-40** Vigor to handle most bosses and challenging enemies comfortably.\n\n### **4. Endurance**\n- **Stamina and Equipment Load:** **Endurance** affects your stamina (used for attacking, dodging, and blocking) and your equipment load (determining your mobility). While not as critical as Intelligence or Mind, maintaining a decent level of Endurance ensures you can dodge effectively and wear necessary gear without being over-encumbered.\n- **Recommended Allocation:** A moderate investment, around **15-20**, should suffice unless you plan to wield heavier equipment or require extensive dodging.\n\n### **5. Attunement (Replaced by Mind in DS3)**\n- **Note:** In Dark Souls 3, the **Attunement** stat from previous titles has been largely replaced by **Mind** for managing FP. So, focus more on Mind rather than allocating points to Attunement.\n\n### **6. Additional Considerations**\n- **Equipment:**\n  - **Catalysts:** Choose a catalyst that scales well with Intelligence, such as the **Black Flame Staff** or **Pyromancer Flame Chart**. Upgrading your catalyst will further boost your spell damage.\n  - **Armor:** Opt for lighter armor to maintain mobility and dodge efficiency. Prioritize gear that offers good protection without significantly increasing your equipment load.\n  \n- **Rings:**\n  - **Spell Damage Enhancers:** Consider rings like the **Bellowing Dragoncrest Ring** to amplify sorcery and pyromancy damage.\n  - **Magick Staff Enhancements:** The **Young Dragon Ring** and **Great Swamp Ring** can also enhance your overall spellcasting effectiveness.\n\n- **Pyromancy Flame Upgrade:**\n  - Make sure to **upgrade your Pyromancy Flame** at a blacksmith. A higher upgrade level directly increases the damage and effectiveness of your pyromancies.\n\n### **7. Balancing Your Build**\nWhile maximizing Intelligence is key, it's important to maintain a balance to ensure your character remains well-rounded:\n- **Survivability:** Don\u2019t neglect Vigor and Endurance; having adequate health and stamina is essential for both offensive and defensive maneuvers.\n- **Flexibility:** Depending on your playstyle, you might want to invest a few points in **Dexterity** or **Strength** if you plan to use melee weapons alongside your pyromancies.\n\n### **8. Gameplay Tips for Pyromancers**\n- **Range Management:** Utilize the range of your pyromancies to control crowds and weaken enemies before engaging in close combat.\n- **FP Management:** Keep an eye on your FP and plan your spell usage to avoid running out during critical moments. Equip talismans or rings that restore FP or reduce spell consumption when possible.\n- **Upgrade Regularly:** Continuously upgrade your catalyst and pyromancy flame to keep your damage output competitive as you progress through the game.\n\n### **Conclusion**\nAn effective pyromancer build in Dark Souls 3 revolves around maximizing **Intelligence** for spell damage, ensuring sufficient **Mind** for casting, and maintaining enough **Vigor** and **Endurance** for survivability and stamina management. By carefully allocating your points and optimizing your equipment, you'll create a powerful pyromancer capable of dealing devastating fire damage while remaining resilient in the face of the game\u2019s challenges.\n\nGood luck on your fiery journey through Lothric!",
